@description.name: @description
@description.body: Creates an RFC4122 compliant UUID/v4 - that means that collisions are possible but highly unlikely (it has been said that "you would need to do-loop uuid() at max speed for 73,067 years for a 50% chance of one collision"). The implementation of this is from https://github.com/jchook/uuid-random
